The paper focuses on the study of exception handling anti-patterns in software development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also analyzes the prevalence of these anti-patterns in Java and C#, which are programming languages (cs.PL). The use of automated exception flow analysis tool suggests a focus on software design (cs.SD) and the potential for improving software reliability (cs.CR). Finally, the study involves data analysis and statistical modeling, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
